Key Match Events: Chris Boucher erupted for five three-pointers and 23 points off the bench.
Scottie Barnes had 24 points and 10 rebounds.
Darius Garland went off for 40 points on 14-for-22 shooting for Cleveland.
RJ Barrett nailed a three-pointer at the halftime buzzer to tie the game at 61.
Toronto hit nine three-pointers in the first half, the same number as Cleveland, but on eight fewer attempts.
Garland hit a three-pointer and free throws in the final minutes to secure the win for Cleveland.
Allen hit a pair of free throws in the final minutes.
Pre-Game Insights: The game was considered a 'trap' game for Cleveland, coming off a win over Oklahoma City.
Cleveland rested scoring leader and top player Donovan Mitchell for the game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Toronto led after the first quarter for the first time since December 22.
Toronto was just the second team to lose 30 games this season after dropping 14-of-15.
